{"key":"processedPost-11085662","value":{"id":11085662,"first":11083973,"last":11086126,"when":1253324895,"utime":"09/19/09 04:48 AM","cleanedPost":"Not only is it not hooked up right, it can't be hooked up right even if you bought an outlet.&nbsp; A switch is in SERIES with the line to the device.&nbsp; It doesn't have the rest of the wires there, unless the switch is fed first, which is rare.&nbsp; Usually they run power to the light box on the ceiling, and then drop a wire to the switch.&nbsp; If there's only one cable entering the light switch box, that's what they did.&nbsp; You can't convert that to an outlet.<br />If all you have is a closet light and switch, simply get one of those outlets that screw into a light bulb socket.&nbsp; It will be hot when the switch is turned on.&nbsp; That is, if those damn things are still legal.&nbsp; They don't have a ground connection.<br />RR"}}